Franklin University offers and delivers Masters of Business Administration (MBA) in partnership with a university in Oman. This MBA program is identical in outcomes and instruction to the domestic based MBA program offered and delivered by Franklin to students in the United States. Franklin University has entered into an agreement to provide online curriculum development, adjunct teaching services, and program installation services to universities in Saudi Arabia. The services provided are identical to the activities performed by Franklin in developing its own curriculum to students in the United States.

Franklin University offers and delivers undergraduate and graduate programs in partnership with a university in South Korea. These programs are identical in outcomes and instruction to the domestic based programs offered and delivered by Franklin to students in the United States.

Franklin University offers and delivers Masters of Business Administration (MBA) in partnership with universities in Poland, Serbia. These MBA programs are identical in outcomes and instruction to the domestic based MBA program offered and delivered by Franklin to students in the United States.

Franklin University has entered into an agreement with a university in Guatemala to review and evaluate its programs. The services provided are identical to the activities performed by Franklin University in reviewing its own curriculum and programs for delivery to students in the United States. Franklin University offers and deliveries Masters of Science in Business Psychology (MSBP) in partnership with universities in Trinidad and Tobago. This MSBP program is identical in outcomes and instruction to the domestic based MSBP program offered and delivered by Franklin to students in the United States.

Graduate Social Work and Education Teaching

Spain-Barcelona: Knox, in cooperation with the University of Barcelona, offers academic study in language, the humanities and the social sciences. Students pursue a combination of courses, all taught in Spanish by professors from the University of Barcelona. Some of the courses are fitted to the particular needs of program students; other courses are from the regular University curriculum offered to Spanish students. All students live in the homes of Spanish families in Barcelona. The program has a two-week trip throughout southern Spain during Winter Break as well as other shorter educational field trips.
